303	  let summary = "Attach static information to an SSA value";
304	  let description = [{
305	    The :code:`assume` operation passes through :code:`value` as the result and
306	    attaches a predicate to it. The assumed predicate is a property of
307	    :code:`result`.
308	
309	    This operation can be used to inject static information into the compiler,
310	    potentially resulting in more efficient code generation.
311	
312	    :code:`predicate` must implement the :code:`AssumePredicateAttrInterface`.
313	
314	    .. note::
315	
316	      :code:`assume` does not check the correctness of the predicate.
317	      Incorrect predicates may inject incorrect static information and cause
318	      miscompilation. If an incorrect predicate is attached to an SSA value,
319	      the behavior of the program is undefined.
320	  }];
321	
